        {
          "type": "user",
          "text": "     1→# Decentralized Twitch (twitch-desent)\n     2→\n     3→## Project Overview\n     4→\n     5→Decentralized streaming platform where **streamers self-host their own servers**. The platform provides either a ready-to-deploy binary (streamer buys domain + VPS, enters data in our installer app like Amnezia, we auto-configure everything) or a managed cloud option (with content moderation — no pirated movies/casinos).\n     6→\n     7→### Key Concept\n     8→Each streamer runs their own Go server (single binary). They can:\n     9→- Add Edge CDN nodes for geo-coverage (e.g., Novosibirsk, St. Petersburg)\n    10→- Host other streamers on their server\n    11→- Register in a Discovery catalog (after moderation) so new viewers can find them\n    12→\n    13→## Architecture\n    14→\n    15→### Video Pipeline\n    16→```\n    17→OBS → RTMP (:1935) → FFmpeg (1080p→720p→480p→360p) → HLS segments (2-4 sec) → HTTP delivery (:443)\n    18→```\n    19→\n    20→### Components (Single Binary)\n    21→- **RTMP Ingest** — accepts OBS stream on port 1935\n    22→- **FFmpeg Transcoder** — multi-quality HLS segmentation\n    23→- **HLS Delivery** — serves `.m3u8` playlists and `.ts` segments via HTTP\n    24→- **WebSocket Chat** — 1 dispatcher goroutine, broadcast to all viewers, rooms per stream\n    25→- **Auth** — JWT-based, middleware on all endpoints\n    26→- **Admin API** — stream settings, CDN node management, user/ban management\n    27→- **SQLite** — local database for users, bans, settings, logs\n    28→\n    29→### External Services (NOT in MVP)\n    30→- **Discovery Service** — cloud catalog of trusted servers (PostgreSQL, moderation)\n    31→- **Edge Nodes** — Go binaries that cache HLS segments from origin server\n    32→\n    33→## Tech Stack\n    34→\n    35→- **Language:** Go 1.23\n    36→- **Database:** SQLite (via `modernc.org/sqlite` — pure Go, no CGO)\n    37→- **HTTP Router:** `net/http` (stdlib, Go 1.22+ routing)\n    38→- **WebSocket:** `nhooyr.io/websocket`\n    39→- **JWT:** `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`\n    40→- **RTMP:** `github.com/nareix/joy5` or custom RTMP listener\n    41→- **Video:** FFmpeg (external process, managed via `os/exec`)\n    42→- **Config:** Environment variables + YAML config file\n    43→\n    44→## Project Structure\n    45→\n    46→```\n    47→twitch-desent/\n    48→├── cmd/\n    49→│   └── server/\n    50→│       └── main.go              # Entry point, wires everything together\n    51→├── internal/\n    52→│   ├── config/\n    53→│   │   └── config.go            # App configuration (env vars only)\n    54→│   ├── auth/\n    55→│   │   ├── handler.go           # POST /api/auth/register, POST /api/auth/login\n    56→│   │   ├── jwt.go               # JWT generation & validation (Claims struct, TokenService)\n    57→│   │   ├── middleware.go         # Auth middleware (extracts user from token)\n    58→│   │   └── store.go             # User storage (SQLite-backed, first user = admin)\n    59→│   ├── chat/\n    60→│   │   ├── hub.go               # Central dispatcher (1 goroutine), session tracking\n    61→│   │   ├── client.go            # Per-connection read/write pumps (nhooyr.io/websocket)\n    62→│   │   ├── handler.go           # WS upgrade endpoint + chat history REST API\n    63→│   │   └── store.go             # stream_sessions + chat_messages CRUD\n    64→│   ├── ingest/\n    65→│   │   ├── manager.go           # FFmpeg subprocess lifecycle, IsLive() status\n    66→│   │   └── ffmpeg.go            # FFmpeg CLI args builder\n    67→│   ├── hls/\n    68→│   │   ├── handler.go           # Serves HLS playlists/segments, stream status endpoint\n    69→│   │   └── cleaner.go           # Periodic cleanup of old HLS segments\n    70→│   ├── admin/\n    71→│   │   └── handler.go           # Admin-only API: settings, bans, CDN config\n    72→│   └── db/\n    73→│       ├── sqlite.go            # Dual-pool DB (write=1 conn, read=4 conns), WAL mode\n    74→│       └── migrations.go        # Schema creation (users, settings, stream_sessions, chat_messages)\n    75→├── static/\n    76→│   └── player.html              # hls.js test player\n    77→├── Dockerfile                   # Multi-stage: golang:1.24-alpine → alpine:3.21 + ffmpeg\n    78→├── docker-compose.yml           # Ports 8080 (HTTP) + 1935 (RTMP)\n    79→├── CLAUDE.md\n    80→├── TODO.md\n    81→├── go.mod\n    82→└── go.sum\n    83→```\n    84→\n    85→## API Endpoints (MVP)\n    86→\n    87→### Auth (no auth required)\n    88→- `POST /api/auth/register` — `{username, password}` → creates user, returns JWT\n    89→- `POST /api/auth/login` — `{username, password}` → validates, returns JWT\n    90→\n    91→### Stream (auth required for some)\n    92→- `GET /live/{quality}/playlist.m3u8` — HLS master/variant playlist (public)\n    93→- `GET /live/{quality}/{segment}.ts` — HLS segment file (public)\n    94→- `GET /api/stream/status` — current stream info (public)\n    95→\n    96→### Chat\n    97→- `WS /ws/chat?token=JWT` — WebSocket connection (auth required, token in query param)\n    98→- `GET /api/chat/history/{sessionId}?limit=50&before=messageId` — chat history (public)\n    99→- `GET /api/chat/sessions?limit=20` — list stream sessions (public)\n   100→\n   101→### Admin (admin auth required)\n   102→- `GET /api/admin/settings` — get server settings\n   103→- `PUT /api/admin/settings` — update server settings\n   104→- `GET /api/admin/users` — list users\n   105→- `POST /api/admin/ban` — ban a user\n   106→- `DELETE /api/admin/ban/{userId}` — unban\n   107→\n   108→## Development Commands\n   109→\n   110→```bash\n   111→# Run the server\n   112→go run ./cmd/server\n   113→\n   114→# Build single binary\n   115→go build -o desent-server ./cmd/server\n   116→\n   117→# Run tests\n   118→go test ./...\n   119→\n   120→# Run with race detector\n   121→go test -race ./...\n   122→```\n   123→\n   124→## MVP Scope\n   125→\n   126→Building the **streamer server only** (single binary). Mocked auth with login/password (real users in SQLite, but no email verification, no OAuth — just username+password→JWT).\n   127→\n   128→### In Scope\n   129→- RTMP ingest + FFmpeg transcoding to HLS\n   130→- HLS segment serving (multi-quality)\n   131→- WebSocket chat with broadcast\n   132→- Auth: register/login with username+password, JWT tokens\n   133→- Admin API (REST, no UI)\n   134→- SQLite storage\n   135→\n   136→### Out of Scope (future)\n   137→- Discovery service (cloud catalog)\n   138→- Edge CDN nodes\n   139→- Admin React SPA\n   140→- OAuth / social login\n   141→- Installer/deployment scripts\n   142→- Content moderation system\n   143→\n   144→## Conventions\n   145→\n   146→- Use Go stdlib where possible (`net/http`, `log/slog`, `encoding/json`)\n   147→- Structured logging with `log/slog`\n   148→- Errors: wrap with `fmt.Errorf(\"context: %w\", err)`\n   149→- No frameworks — keep dependencies minimal\n   150→- Tests alongside code (`*_test.go` in same package)\n   151→- Context propagation through all handlers\n   152→- Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n   153→\n   154→## Codebase Patterns\n   155→\n   156→### Module Wiring\n   157→Each package follows the pattern: `NewStore(db)` → `NewHandler(store, deps)` → `handler.RegisterRoutes(mux)`.\n   158→All wiring happens in `cmd/server/main.go`. No dependency injection framework — explicit construction.\n   159→\n   160→### Database Access\n   161→- `db.DB` has `.Write` (1 conn) and `.Read` (4 conns) pools — use Write for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE, Read for SELECT\n   162→- SQLite with WAL mode, foreign keys enabled, 5s busy timeout\n   163→- Schema in `internal/db/migrations.go` as a single `const schema` string executed on startup\n   164→- Timestamps stored as Unix epoch integers via `DEFAULT (unixepoch())`\n   165→\n   166→### Auth Flow\n   167→- `auth.TokenService` generates/validates JWT tokens with `Claims{UserID, Username, Role}`\n   168→- First registered user auto-promoted to admin role\n   169→- WS auth: JWT passed as `?token=` query param (browser WS API can't set headers)\n   170→- HTTP auth: JWT in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header, extracted by `auth.Middleware`\n   171→\n   172→### Chat Architecture\n   173→- Hub pattern: single goroutine event loop (select on register/unregister/broadcast/ticker/ctx.Done)\n   174→- Hub polls `ingest.Manager.IsLive()` every 2s to auto-create/close `stream_sessions`\n   175→- Messages persisted only when stream is live (sessionID > 0)\n   176→- Client has separate readPump (reads JSON from WS) and writePump (writes from send channel) goroutines\n   177→- Rate limiting: per-client, configurable via `CHAT_RATE_LIMIT_MS` (default 500ms)\n   178→- Message length cap: `CHAT_MAX_MSG_LEN` (default 500 chars, truncated silently)\n   179→- JSON wire format: `{\"type\":\"chat\"|\"system\", \"text\":\"...\", \"user_id\":N, \"username\":\"...\", \"timestamp\":N}`\n   180→\n   181→### Config\n   182→All config via environment variables with sensible defaults. `getEnv(key, fallback)` and `getEnvInt(key, fallback)` helpers.\n   183→\n   184→### Ingest/Streaming\n   185→- `ingest.Manager.Run(ctx)` — infinite loop: start FFmpeg with `-listen 1`, wait for exit, restart after 2s\n   186→- `Manager.IsLive()` returns `running` field (protected by mutex), set true on FFmpeg start, false on exit\n   187→- `LiveChecker` interface (defined in `hls` and `chat` packages) — `IsLive() bool`\n   188→- HLS cleaner runs as background goroutine, removes old `.ts` segments\n   189→",
